            <section id="ph-myth" class="mb-12">
                <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-6 md:p-8">
                    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#118AB2] mb-4">The Acidity Question: A pH Primer</h2>
                    <p class="mb-6 text-base">A common concern about Coca-Cola is its low pH, making it highly acidic. While this acidity is a real factor for dental health, it's not the primary threat to your body's internal systems. Your stomach is naturally more acidic to digest food, and your body has powerful mechanisms to maintain a stable internal pH balance.</p>
                    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-center">
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-center">Comparing pH Levels</h3>
                            <p class="text-sm text-center mb-4 text-gray-600">Lower pH means higher acidity. While Coke is acidic, your stomach acid is far more potent.</p>
                            <div class="chart-container h-64 md:h-[300px]">
                                <canvas id="phChart"></canvas>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="text-center bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-[#FFD166] p-6 rounded-lg">
                            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#073B4C]">The Real Damage: Dental Erosion</h3>
                             <p class="icon-unicode mt-4 mb-2">ü¶∑</p>
                            <p class="text-base">The primary danger of cola's acidity is to your teeth. The phosphoric and citric acids can erode tooth enamel, especially with frequent consumption. This erosion softens the tooth surface, making it more susceptible to cavities and decay.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            
            <section id="sugar-tsunami" class="mb-12">
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center text-[#FF6B6B] mb-6">The Real Culprit: The Sugar Tsunami</h2>
                 <p class="text-lg text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">If pH isn't the main systemic problem, what is? The overwhelming scientific consensus points to one ingredient above all others: sugar. The amount of sugar in a single can of cola is staggering and has profound effects on the body.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                    <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-6 md:p-8 text-center flex flex-col justify-center items-center">
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#073B4C]">In a Single 12oz (355ml) Can:</h3>
                        <p class="text-8xl md:text-9xl font-black text-[#FF6B6B] my-4">39g</p>
                        <p class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[#073B4C]">of Added Sugar</p>
                        <p class="text-xl mt-4 text-gray-600">That's equivalent to nearly <span class="font-bold">10 teaspoons</span>.</p>
                        <div class="text-4xl mt-4 text-[#FF6B6B]" aria-hidden="true">
                            <span>ü•Ñ</span><span>ü•Ñ</span><span>ü•Ñ</span><span>ü•Ñ</span><span>ü•Ñ</span><span>ü•Ñ</span><span>ü•Ñ</span><span>ü•Ñ</span><span>ü•Ñ</span><span>ü•Ñ</span>
