        <footer class="text-center mt-12 py-8 border-t border-gray-200">
            <p class="text-lg font-bold text-[#073B4C]">The Takeaway: Moderation is Key</p>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto mt-2">While an occasional soda is unlikely to cause major harm, regular consumption poses significant, well-documented health risks that go far beyond its pH level. The primary driver of these risks is its extremely high concentration of added sugar. Making informed choices and prioritizing water and other unsweetened beverages is crucial for long-term health.</p>
             <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-8">Data sourced from studies published by the World Health Organization, CDC, and various peer-reviewed medical journals. This infographic is for informational purposes only.</p>
